<TITLE> Khaleda asks OIC to strengthen Al-Quds Committee </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 5 (bdnews24.com)--Opposition chief Khaleda Zia has asked the Organisation of Islamic Conference to strengthen the Al-Quds Committee to resolve the problems of the Palestine people. She made the call at a meeting with the visiting OIC chief Eklmeluddin Ihsanulgul on Thursday evening at her Gulshan office. The BNP chief's foreign affairs advisor Shamser Mobin Chowdhury told journalists, "It was a courtesy call. The OIC chief briefed former prime minister Khaleda Zia about activities of the organisation." During the 40-minute meeting, Khaleda called the OIC to rev up the operations of the Al-Quds Committee formed under OIC in order to facilitate an independent Palestine state and fix the problems of the muslims living there, he added. She appreciated the role of OIC in establishing peace among Muslim countries and hoped that the chief bloc of Islamic states will work more effectively in the days ahead. BNP general secratery Khandakar Delwar Hossain and another adviser Reaz Rahman were also present in the meeting. bdnews
